The differential of $h$ along the direction $\mathbf{Z}$ is 
$$
\text{D} h(\mathbf{X})[\mathbf{Z}] = \mathbf{X}^\top \mathbf{Z} + \mathbf{Z}^\top \mathbf{X} + 
2\mathbf{P} \text{diag}(\mathbf{X}^\top \mathbf{Z}) \mathbf{P} - \mathbf{P}(\mathbf{X}^\top \mathbf{Z} + \mathbf{Z}^\top \mathbf{X}) \mathbf{P}.
$$
