# Empirical applications

## Multitrait-multimethod modeling

@watts_2021 used a confirmatory multitrait-multimethod (MTMM) model to investigate two traits (i.e., Internalizing and Externalizing) in a samples of youths (*N* = 2119) for whom three informants reported on the youth’s psychopathology (i.e., child, parents, and teachers).

We reanalyzed the data by fitting an exploratory MTMM model with target rotation. We used a partially oblique rotation where the method factors and trait factors were freed to correlate among themselves but not between. In other words, the method factors were orthogonal to the trait factors.

